<br>
By tha same token, outer guards ar elite sa they can better protect tha youngins, but if they arent tough enough ta survive, than tha youngins better learn fast, cos tha world outside isnt gonna hold yer hand, if ya know wot ahm sayin.<br>
<br>
Life is grim sometimes. If ya dont like it when someone calls reinforcements fer tha guards, I suggest ya dont kill guards. And if yer ah youngin, and ya dont like not havin guards ta run ta, I suggest ya call fer reinforcements.<br>
<br>
*smiles and folds his arms resolutely* All part ov survival as ah see it.<br>
<br>
Buran McMuffin, the original Iron Chef<br>
&quot;Slayin gnolls n makin muffins since 3174.&quot;<br>
<br>
ooc: I know its against VI policy to train guards, but I think it is suspect for people to hunt guards and then whine about getting trained. Malicious training in other zones is an entirely different matter in my mind... It is highly unrealistic to expect that you should be able to pick apart a society's defenses completely on your terms, without those defenses adapting, and quickly, to such threats. Look at how quickly societies adapt in the real world to such threats... Ive never hunted guards before, but if I ever do, I wont complain about getting trained. Its all part of the give and take of daily life.<br>
<br>
